@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Plastic_Impact";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<!--Plastic Impact Banner Block-->
<div class="banner">
    <div class="plastic-impact-banner-block"></div>
    <div class="banner-text-block">
        <h1 class="banner_text_color" style="font-size:30px;font-weight:bold">Plastic Impact</h1>
    </div>
</div>

<!--Plastic Impact Banner Block-->
<div class="container">
    <!--Plastic Impact Section-->
    <div class="site-half plastic-gif-block" id="start">
        <div class="left">
            <img class="img-bg-1 plastic-impact_img" src="~/images/Plastic-Impact.gif" />
        </div>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row no-gutters align-items-stretch">
                <div class="col-lg-5 ml-lg-auto py-5">
                    <!--<span class="caption d-block mb-2 font-secondary font-weight-bold">Impact of Plastic Packaging</span>-->
                    <p>Such a useful thing as plastic, that already has become an integral part of our everyday life, is actually highly dangerous for our environment.</p>
                    <p>Not only it is harmful to animals, but it is also the main source of fracking. Secondly, plastic contributes a lot to CO2 emissions. Moreover, plastic has begun to enter the food chain and it ends up on our plates.</p>
                    <p>Have you ever thought about how much plastic we consume? Think about it next time you go to a supermarket to get some food.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="site-half block line-chart-block">
        <canvas id="line-chart" class="img-bg-1 right col-12" style="position:center;height:350px"></canvas>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row no-gutters align-items-stretch">
                <div class="col-lg-5 mr-lg-auto py-5">
                    <!--<span class="caption d-block mb-2 font-secondary font-weight-bold">Impact of Plastic Packaging</span>-->
                    <p>From berries to meat, from fresh to frozen produce, everything is packed in plastic. As of 2018 almost 3.5 millions of plastic waste was produced in Australia and less that 5% of it was actually recycled.</p>
                    <p>Where did the rest go? Landfill, oceans, you name it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!--Plastic Impact Section-->
</div>

<!--YouTube Vedio for introducting why reduce plastic-->
<div class="col-12" style="margin-top:100px">
    <center>
        <h2>Why do we need to reduce plastic</h2>
        <iframe style="width:80%;height:500px" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Yomf5pBN8dY" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

    </center>
</div>

<!--Data Visualisation script-->
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@2.8.0"></script>
<script>
    new Chart(document.getElementById("line-chart"), {
        type: 'bar',
        data: {
            labels: ['2014 - 15', '2015 - 16', '2016 - 17', '2017 - 18'],

            datasets: [{
                type: "line",
                data: [160533.84, 149127.57, 130695.1, 137167.42],
                label: 'Plastic waste recovered for reprocessing',
                borderColor: "#3e95cd",
                fill: false
            }, {
                type: "bar",
                label: "Plastic waste produced",
                borderColor: "ffff00",
                data: [3167000, 2912000, 2955400, 3407300],
                fill: false
            }]
        },
        options: {
            responsive: false,
            title: {
                display: true,
                text: "Comparison of platic waste produced vs recycled in Australia"

            }
        }

    });
</script>
